A 'Sympetrum danae' is a species of dragonfly belonging to the family Libellulidae. 
It is commonly known as the Black Darter or the Black Meadowhawk. 
It has a slender and elongated body with black and yellow stripes on the abdomen. 
The wings of 'Sympetrum danae' are transparent with black veins. 
The male dragonfly has red eyes while the female has yellowish brown eyes. 
'Sympetrum danae' can be commonly found near ponds, lakes, and other slow-moving water bodies. 
This species of dragonfly is commonly found in Europe and Asia.
